---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About - txtui"
  description="About txtui - Plain text UI components for AI agents"
  jsonLd={{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    name: "About - txtui",
    url: "https://txtui.dev/about/",
    description: "About txtui - Plain text UI components for AI agents",
  }}
>
  <header class="mt-6 mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">About</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong>txtui</strong> is a catalog of plain text UI components designed for
      AI agents.
    </p>

    <p>
      When working with AI agents, sharing a visual image of a UI component can
      be difficult. txtui provides ready-to-copy text-based UI components that
      you can paste directly into your conversations with AI agents to quickly
      communicate your design intent.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Why txtui?</h2>

    <p>
      When you ask an AI agent to build a UI, describing what you want in words
      often leads to misunderstanding and multiple rounds of revision. txtui
      solves this by giving you ready-made text-based UI components that you can
      paste directly into your prompt.
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-muted mt-4">
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Smoother communication</span> — Share the intent of
        individual UI parts clearly with AI agents — just copy and paste.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Fewer iterations</span> — A concrete visual reference
        helps the AI reach the desired output in fewer rounds.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Save tokens</span> — Plain text uses far fewer tokens
        than image analysis, and fewer iterations means even more savings.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Works anywhere</span> — Plain text works in CLI tools,
        API calls, and any chat interface — no image support required.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Technology agnostic</span> — You don't need to know
        HTML, SwiftUI, or any specific framework to communicate your design.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to use</h2>

    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-text-muted">
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Browse</span> the component catalog on the top page
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Filter</span> by tags to find the component you need
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Copy</span> the variation that matches your intent
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Paste</span> it into your AI agent conversation
      </li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</Layout>
